================================================================================
  MASCOT & VISUAL IDENTITY
================================================================================

  MASCOT: "Vrr" -- an abstract wave-form character that shifts shape.
  Part sound wave, part friendly creature. Pulses and oscillates.
  Task completion = wave gets smoother. Tasks pile up = wave gets
  jittery. Or: NO mascot. Pure abstract. VYBRR as a FEELING.

  COLORS:
    Primary: Deep purple (#6200EA) to cyan (#00BCD4) gradient
    Secondary: Midnight (#121212)
    Accent: Warm coral (#FF6B6B)

  LOGO: Letters VYBRR where the Y forms a sound wave peak.
  Gradient-heavy. Glassmorphism. Dark mode default.

  ANIMATION:
    Everything pulses gently. Subtle heartbeat animation on tasks.
    Completing a task sends out a ripple wave.
    The app breathes with you.

================================================================================
  SONIC BRANDING
================================================================================

  Notification: A warm, resonant "hum" rising in pitch. Like a tuning
  fork finding its note. Not a beep. A vibration.
  Sonic logo: Bass note swells into a chord, then soft "click."
  Task done: Bell-like tone with reverb. Musical satisfaction.
  Ambient mode: Lo-fi frequencies, binaural beats during focus time.

================================================================================
  CULTURAL RESONANCE
================================================================================

  US:      "Vibe" = most deeply embedded Gen Z word globally.
           "Vibe check" is universal. Double-R signals tech product.
  INDIA:   "Vibe hai" (it has vibes) = common Hindi slang. Vibration
           connects to spiritual/yoga concepts (chakra frequencies).
  UK:      "Vibes" well-understood. Double-R pattern is established.
  JAPAN:   "Baibusu" (vibes) entered Japanese slang via Terrace House.
  BRAZIL:  "Boa vibe" (good vibes) = common Brazilian Portuguese slang.

