================================================================================
  MASCOT & VISUAL IDENTITY
================================================================================

  MASCOT OPTION A: "Jynxi" -- a small, mischievous imp that represents
  the jinx (the spirit of forgetfulness). It tries to steal your tasks.
  The app catches it and puts tasks back. The antagonist mascot.

  MASCOT OPTION B: "Hex" -- a friendly owl-wizard (owls = wisdom,
  Duolingo proved owls work) wearing a tiny wizard hat with circuit-
  board constellations. Hex watches over your tasks and casts
  protective spells (reminders).

  COLORS:
    Primary: Midnight purple (#1A0033)
    Secondary: Electric gold (#FFD700)
    Accent: Enchantment blue (#4FC3F7)
    Background: Star-field patterns, mystical but modern

  LOGO: "UN" in a shield/circle (the protection spell), "JYNX" below.
  The X forms a crossed-wands motif. Rune-inspired iconography.

  ANIMATION:
    Tasks appear on "scroll" cards with parchment texture.
    Completion = spell-burst of sparkles and golden light.
    Reminder arrives with a mystical shimmer.
    All-done state: aurora animation across the screen.

================================================================================
  SONIC BRANDING
================================================================================

  Notification: Crystalline bells with slight reverb. Like a spell
  activating. Magical chime.
  Sonic logo: Descending mysterious note (jinx arriving) -> ascending
  bright chord (the unjinx). Musical drama in 2 seconds.
  Task done: Sparkly "spell success" shimmer. Like a power-up.
  Reminder: Low mystical hum that builds. The spell is activating.

================================================================================
  CULTURAL RESONANCE
================================================================================

  US:      "Jinx" = childhood game, sports superstitions, universally
           understood. Fantasy/gaming culture (D&D, Harry Potter, Marvel)
           = massive audience alignment.
  INDIA:   "Nazar" (evil eye) culture is deeply rooted. "Nazar utaro"
           (ward off the evil eye). UNJYNX = the nazar protection
           for your schedule. INCREDIBLY strong cultural hook.
  UK:      "Touch wood" culture. Harry Potter is BRITISH -- the entire
           spell/enchantment vocabulary is native.
  JAPAN:   "Omamori" (protective charms), "yakuyoke" (warding off evil).
           Protective charm for your tasks = deep cultural resonance.
  BRAZIL:  "Quebranto" (curse), "simpatias" (counter-spells). Vibrant
           superstition culture. Un-cursing forgetfulness resonates.

